 a grin, her ponytail visible down her back.\n\nThe commercial shifts to a clean demonstration on a pale gray surface divided by a vertical white line. On the left, a label reads “Leading Ordinary Brand” with smaller text indicating a full-size sheet. On the right, a label shows “Select-A-Size Bounty.” Identical-looking amber spills sit on both sides. Hands in white sleeves place paper towel sheets over the spills. The left sheet is larger; the right sheet is smaller. As the hands press down, a blue graphic appears on the Bounty side reading “50% More Absorbent.” The towels soak up the liquid while the hands rub and press. The left side looks wetter and more spread out, while the Bounty side appears to gather the spill into the smaller sheet. When the sheets are lifted, both show dark amber stains where the liquid has been absorbed.\n\nThe final product display appears against a bright green background. A white paper towel roll stands upright on a silver holder, with a stepped stack of smaller Select-A-Size sheets shown beside it. The sheets slide away, leaving the roll centered. Large white text appears to the right: “The small but POWERFUL PICKER-UPPER,” with “POWERFUL” emphasized in bigger, bolder letters.",
